"a.对角的；n.对角线 【英】 对角的(crossing a straight-side figure, eg a rectangle, from corner to corner) 【考】 diameter : circle / diagonal : rectangle(直径是圆形内最长直 线/对角线是矩形内最 长直线) adj. 对角的; n 对角线 【记】dia, 2, gon角－2角之间的线－对角线 【类】diameter: circle = diagonal: rectangle直径是圆形内最长直线 = 对角线是矩形内最长直线 【记】dia 通过，横过 + gon 角→对角 【相关】pentagon 五角大楼，polygon 多角形，trigon 三角形 diagonal (adj.)  1540s (implied in diagonally), from Middle French diagonal, from Latin diagonalis, from diagonus ""slanting line,"" from Greek diagonios ""from angle to angle,"" from dia- ""across"" (see dia-) + gonia ""angle,"" related to gony ""knee"" (see knee (n.)). As a noun, from 1570s."
